20/09/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government and the United States signed an agreement Friday (17 September) enhancing bilateral co-operation in drug control and law enforcement.
The document represents an addendum to an earlier bilateral memorandum of understanding initialled in July.
The agreement provides for US assistance with two new projects worth a total of 2.5m euros.
In other news, French diplomat Pierre Moscovici has been appointed as the new European Parliament rapporteur for Romania.
He replaces Baroness Emma Nicholson.
(Rompres, Mediafax - 20/09/04;
Rompres - 17/09/04)
